com.esri.mo2.cs.geod
Class ReferencedDatum

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.esri.mo2.cs.geod.BaseNamedGeodeticObject
        |
        +--com.esri.mo2.cs.geod.ReferencedDatum
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Equivalency, GeodeticObject, NamedObject
public class ReferencedDatum
extends BaseNamedGeodeticObject
implements Equivalency

Implements a ReferencedDatum for the geodesy package. A referenced datum is a datum which is related to WGS84. This relationship is specified by the datum transformation between WGS84 and the referenced datum.

AXL

  • <REFDATUM name="ADINDAN-MEAN" desc="Adindan-Mean" longdesc="Used primarily in Africa" class="Molodensky" dx="-166" dy="-15" dz="204" >
  • <ELLIPSOID a="6378249.145" inverseF="293.465" />
  • </REFDATUM> where
  • name is the referenced datum name
  • desc is the referenced datum description
  • longdesc is the referenced datum's long description
  • class is the class name of the datum transformation
  • The following are specific to the Molodensky transformation:
  • dx is x-translation in meters
  • dy is y-translation in meters
  • dz is z-translation in meters
    • ELLIPSOID (see Ellipsoid AXL documentation)

    • If the name is only given (class is not given), the geodetic database is accessed for the referenced datum instantiation (and no ellipsoid is needed). If class is given, the database is not accessed and the name, description and long description fields are optional attributes. Some examples of this are:

  • <REFDATUM name="ADINDAN-MEAN" />

  • <REFDATUM class="Molodensky" dx="-166" dy="-15" dz="204" >
  • <ELLIPSOID a="6378249.145" inverseF="293.465" />
  • </REFDATUM>

    Partial Referenced Datum Table from the Geodetic Database:

  • [$Referenced Datums$, ReferencedDatum]
  • //NAME, DESCRIPTION, LONG DESCRIPTION, DATUM TRANS TYPE NAME, ELLIPSOID, DATUM TRANS INSTANCE DATA, PRIME MERIDAN (ASSUMED GREENWICH)
  • ADINDAN-MEAN, "Adindan - Mean", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -166, -15, 204
  • ADINDAN-BF, "Adindan - Burkina Faso", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -118, -14, 218
  • ADINDAN-CAMEROON, "Adindan - Cameroon", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -134, -2, 210
  • ADINDAN-ETHIOPIA, "Adindan - Ethiopia", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -165, -11, 206
  • ADINDAN-MALI, "Adindan - Mali", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -123, -20, 220
  • ADINDAN-SENEGAL, "Adindan - Senegal", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -128, -18, 224
  • ADINDAN-SUDAN, "Adindan - Sudan", "", MOLODENSKY, CLARKE 1880, -161, -14, 205
  • AFGOOYE-SOMALIA, "Afgooye - Somalia", "", MOLODENSKY, KRASSOVSKY, -43, -163, 45
  • AGD66, "Australian Geodetic Datum 1966", "", BURSA,AUSTRALIAN,-137.882,-50.47,137.19,0.015,0.591,-0.298,-1.017

    DatumTransformation, Ellipsoid
